{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-06-12-2",
 "title": "Sizing Up the Spychief",
 "summary": "At the Coronet City spaceport, the Sarian Commodore Ernie Pallando, having just parted from Josh Arands, spots the New Republic Intelligence captain Jonau Diggs sitting on a bench reading a book and smoking a cigar, utterly absorbed and oblivious. Pallando circles around to startle the old spy with a tap on the shoulder, but the unflappable Diggs barely reacts, trading dry, fatalistic banter about his own failing health and long years of service. Pallando admits he sought Diggs out to take the measure of the man who will be watching his back on an upcoming intelligence mission, and the two agree to talk more in two days at the embassy. They part with guarded courtesy, Diggs quietly wondering whether the man who crept up on him is truly an ally as he returns to his book.",
